# Cursor Rules for brillQ Website

## General Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow Next.js 14 App Router conventions
- Use server components by default, add 'use client' only when needed
- Prefer Tailwind CSS utility classes over custom CSS
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Component Guidelines
- Create small, reusable components
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces
- Add proper accessibility attributes (aria-labels, roles)
- Ensure keyboard navigation support
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion for animations

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use the defined color palette from tailwind.config.ts
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale
- Use custom classes defined in globals.css when appropriate

## Animation Guidelines
- Use Framer Motion for complex animations
- Implement scroll-triggered animations with IntersectionObserver
- Always check for reduced motion preferences
- Keep animations subtle and purposeful
- Use consistent timing and easing functions

## Performance Guidelines
- Use next/image for all images
- Implement lazy loading for below-the-fold content
- Minimize client-side JavaScript
- Use ISR or SSG where appropriate
- Optimize bundle size

## SEO Guidelines
- Add proper meta tags to all pages
- Include JSON-LD structured data
- Generate dynamic sitemaps
- Use semantic HTML structure
- Implement proper heading hierarchy

## Accessibility Guidelines
- Ensure keyboard navigation works everywhere
- Add proper ARIA labels and roles
- Maintain proper color contrast ratios
- Provide text alternatives for images
- Test with screen readers

## Code Organization
- Group related components in folders
- Keep utility functions in lib/utils
- Use barrel exports (index.ts) for cleaner imports
- Separate business logic from presentation
- Keep components under 200 lines when possible

